The paper discusses an application of Answer Set Programming (ASP) to understand narratives about stereotypical activities, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ASP for question answering also suggests a connection to Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of hierarchical plans and reasoning about normal and exceptional scenarios, which are topics related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the understanding of narratives, which could potentially involve issues related to Cybersecurity (cs.CR).
